Nguyen Anh Tuan is a Fresher Game Developer with 0 years of commercial experience. Their core expertise lies in Game Development, utilizing Finite State Machine and Object-Oriented Programming concepts, with a strong foundation in Unity and C# programming language. They have developed multiple personal projects, including a role-play farming game, a 2D UI-focused quiz game, and a 2D Mario-like tile-based game, demonstrating their ability to design and implement interactive game mechanics, character interactions, and scene consistency. These projects showcase their proficiency in Unity and C#, with a focus on game development principles and techniques.

Technically, Nguyen Anh Tuan is proficient in C# programming language and has hands-on experience with Unity framework, leveraging its capabilities to create immersive gaming experiences. They have a solid understanding of game development concepts, including character finite state machines, item and inventory management, NPC dialog systems, and combat mechanics. Their experience with Unity's tile and tilemap system, as well as its UI system, has equipped them with the skills to design and develop engaging 2D games. With a strong educational background in Computer Science from Ton Duc Thang University, Nguyen Anh Tuan possesses a deep understanding of programming principles, data structures, and software engineering concepts, making them a promising candidate for game development roles.